# Pin this repository to the public npm registry.
# Per docs/strategy/public-boundary-STRATEGY.md, this is a public repo and the
# package-lock.json must contain only public registry URLs (no internal Nexus
# proxies, no organizational identifiers).
#
# Developers using an internal mirror locally can override via ~/.npmrc, but
# this file ensures CI and any contributor with a default npm config gets the
# public registry — and that the committed lockfile reflects it.
registry=https://registry.npmjs.org/
